@notice The (older) MasterChef contract gives out a constant number of SUSHI tokens per block.
 It is the only address with minting rights for SUSHI.
 The idea for this MasterChef V2 (MCV2) contract is therefore to be the owner of a dummy token
 that is deposited into the MasterChef V1 (MCV1) contract.
 The allocation point for this pool on MCV1 is the total allocation point for all pools that receive double incentives.
@notice Address of SUSHI contract.
@notice Info of each MCV2 pool.
@notice Address of the LP token for each MCV2 pool.
@notice Address of each `IRewarder` contract in MCV2.
@notice Info of each user that stakes LP tokens.
@dev Tokens added
@dev Total allocation points. Must be the sum of all allocation points in all pools.
@param _sushi The SUSHI token contract address.

userdoc.notice: The (older) MasterChef contract gives out a constant number of SUSHI tokens per block. It is the only address with minting rights for SUSHI. The idea for this MasterChef V2 (MCV2) contract is therefore to be the owner of a dummy token that is deposited into the MasterChef V1 (MCV1) contract. The allocation point for this pool on MCV1 is the total allocation point for all pools that receive double incentives.
